Sure, here are some examples of sentences in Serbian that use the word "lijep" in different forms and positions, with translations in English in parentheses:

1. *Lijep*a kuća ima veliku baštu. (A *beautiful* house has a large garden.)
2. Imala je *lijep*o lice sa prekrasnim osmijehom. (She had a *pretty* face with a beautiful smile.)
3. *Lijep* je danas dan za šetnju parkom. (It's *nice* weather today for a walk in the park.)
4. Dala mi je *lijep*u knjigu na poklon. (She gave me a *nice* book as a gift.)
5. Njihov domaćin bio je *lijep* prema svim gostima. (Their host was *kind* to all guests.)
6. *Lijep*im riječima možeš mnogo postići. (With *pleasant* words, you can achieve a lot.)
7. Vidio sam *lijep*e slike na tvojoj izložbi. (I saw *beautiful* pictures at your exhibition.)
8. On je *lijep*o pjevao na koncertu sinoć. (He *sang* beautifully at the concert last night.)
9. Sve više ljudi se odlučuje za *lijep*e ručno izrađene predmete. (More and more people are choosing *beautiful* handmade items.)
10. *Lijep*a žena je bila glavna glumica u tom filmu. (A *gorgeous* woman was the main actress in that movie.)